      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed at 2.5, 3.0, 4.0, and 5.0 L/min operating points. GCI values ranged from 1.8% to 3.9%, all below the 5% threshold. Fine mesh (8.2M cells) selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match CFD boundary conditions within ±5% for flow rate and ±1% for rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted using porcine blood analog at 37°C. Flow rates controlled by Coriolis flowmeter (±0.5% accuracy). Rotational speed verified by optical tachometer (±0.2%). All nominal operating points confirmed within acceptance tolerances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Relative error between CFD-predicted and measured RH index must be < 10% at all validated operating points.",
      "rationale": "RH index relative errors at five validated operating points ranged from 2.4% to 4.2%, all well below the 10% acceptance threshold. Model demonstrates adequate predictive accuracy across the nominal operating band."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
