      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest must directly support the hemolysis worst-case identification decision.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary regulatory metric for CPB device hemolysis comparison. CFD outputs (shear stress fields, exposure time distributions) are directly integrated into the power-law hemolysis model to compute RH. QoI selection is directly relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same pump geometry, fluid properties, and operating regime as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry identical to the COU model. Blood analog viscosity and density matched COU simulation inputs. Operating points span the nominal CPB flow range of 2.1–5.0 L/min. High-shear blade-tip regions and extreme low-flow weaning conditions (below 2.0 L/min) were studied separately and are not included in this validation dataset; those edge-case results will be incorporated in a future credibility update."
